                    <div class="tab-pane fade in active" id="connect">
                     <p>
                      TRB's work relies on volunteers and seeks to involve transportation professionals at every stage of their career. Get involved by receiving updates, volunteering, or responding to proposals:
                     </p>
                     <ul>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/Contact/Contact.aspx">
                        Contact staff
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/Publications/PubsTRBENewsletter.aspx">
                        Subscribe to the E-Newsletter
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/ElectronicSessions/Twitter.aspx">
                        Follow us on Social Media
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/GetInvolvedwithTRB/volunteer.aspx">
                        Volunteer
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/publications/pubstrnewsmagazine.aspx">
                        Read the TR News
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/GetInvolvedwithTRB/propose.aspx">
                        Respond to Requests for Proposals
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="https://careers.mytrb.org/">
                        Visit the Job Center
                       </a>
                      </li>
                     </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="convene">
                     <p>
                      TRB’s community links thousands of passionate transportation professionals from around the world, which strengthens personal and professional connections, supports dialogue and establishes information-exchange. Learn about TRB’s:
                     </p>
                     <ul>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/AboutTRB/StandingCommitteesMT.aspx">
                        Standing Committees
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/AnnualMeeting/AnnualMeeting.aspx">
                        Annual Meeting
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/Calendar/Calendar.aspx">
                        Conferences and Webinars
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/AboutTRB/MinorityStudent.aspx">
                        Minority Student Fellows Program
                       </a>
                      </li>
                     </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="research">
                     <p>
                      Through an objective and interdisciplinary approach, TRB stimulates research on topics that will have the greatest impact on transportation. TRB’s research includes practical and ready-to-implement products, a bibliographic database, and a peer-reviewed journal. Learn more about:
                     </p>
                     <ul>
                      <li>
                       <a href="https://trid.trb.org/">
                        TRID
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://trrjournalonline.trb.org/">
                        Transportation Research Record: Journal of the Transportation Research Board
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/NCHRP/NCHRP.aspx">
                        National Cooperative Highway Research Program (NCHRP)
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/TCRP/TCRP.aspx">
                        Transit Cooperative Research Program (TCRP)
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/ACRP/ACRP.aspx">
                        Airport Cooperative Research Program (ACRP)
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/NCFRP/NCFRP.aspx">
                        National Cooperative Freight Research Program (NCFRP)
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/HMCRP/HMCRP.aspx">
                        Hazardous Materials Cooperative Research Program (HMCRP)
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/NCRRP/NCRRP.aspx">
                        National Cooperative Rail Research Program (NCRRP)
                       </a>
                      </li>
                     </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="advise">
                     <p>
                      Since 1982, TRB has conducted more than 100 studies at the request of Congress, executive-branch federal agencies, the states, and other organizations, providing objective and interdisciplinary advice on complex and controversial transportation topics. Learn about TRB’s:
                     </p>
                     <ul>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/PolicyStudies/PolicyStudies.aspx">
                        Studies and Special Programs
                       </a>
                      </li>
                      <li>
                       <a href="http://www.trb.org/MarineBoard/Public/MarineBoard.aspx">
                        Marine Board
                       </a>
                      </li>
                     </ul>
